[[Category:Lists of Sites of Special Scientific Interest]] [[Category:Conservation in the United Kingdom]] [[Category:Lists of protected areas of the United Kingdom]]

The following list shows the readings of the maximum and minimum temperatures for each year from 1862 to the present, recorded in the weather station of the [[Collegio Romano]] in [[Rome]], established in 1788.<ref>[http://www.rinnovabili.it/storico/osservatorio-meteorologico-romano-ieri-oggi-e-per-fortuna-domani/ Osservatorio Meteorologico Romano: ieri, oggi e, per fortuna, domani]</ref> The station, actually located in the [[Italy|Italian territory]], was opened when Rome was part of the [[Papal States]]. The first weather station in the Vatican state<ref>[http://www.vaticanstate.va/content/vaticanstate/en/meteo.html Vatican City State Weather Station Data]</ref> was opened only in 2009, and is placed in the Palace of the Governorate of Vatican City.<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2009/06/04/blogs/oltretevere/stazione-meteo-in-vaticano-70XZGYV6mUz3JEQeu31aKI/pagina.html Stazione meteo in Vaticano]</ref>
